DESCRIPTION:Tickets $25\nPurchase Tickets\nChoreographer working with movement and sound presents new work for her Roulette Commission.\n\nJessica Cook shares new material developed as part of her Roulette Commission.\n*FREE FOR ALL ROULETTE MEMBERS *\nA livestream will be available free of charge at 8pm on the day of the performance and archived for future viewing.\nUSE CODE EARLYBIRDER AT CHECKOUT FOR $5 OFF FALL TICKETS — ENDS AUGUST 31ST.\nJessica Cook\nis a Brooklyn based choreographer working with movement and sound to create a felt absurdity. She has presented her work in venues such as La MaMa Moves Festival\, LMCC’s RIver to River Festival\, Roulette Intermedium\, Movement Research at Judson Memorial Church\, and many\, many AUNTS shows. She has been an artist-in-residence at The Chocolate Factory Theater\, Movement Research\, NY Live Arts Fresh Tracks\, and MoMA PS1. She is a 2005 graduate of the SUNY Purchase Dance Conservatory.
DURATION:PT2H
LOCATION:Roulette Intermedium\, 509 Atlantic Ave\, Brooklyn\, NY
DTSTART:20261120T010000Z
SUMMARY:Jessica Cook (Night 1)
UID:f4944cc2-a026-4118-bb16-a720ab46a209@f494.org
